@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@{u}@{fg shine}Usage:@{uu}@{fg text} Mousepos Cmd/K,XOffset/K/N,YOffset/K/N


Cmd/K       : execute a command, script or whatever

XOffset/K   : offset mouse x position

YOffset/K   : offset mouse y position


@{"Examples" link "Examples" 0}:
@endnode

@node "Examples" "Examples"
@{fg shine}mousepos cmd="echo $mousex"@{fg text}

 >would echo the mouse x position

---------------------------------------------------------------

@{fg shine}mousepos cmd="newshell window=con:$mousex/$mousey/640/100/test/CLOSE"
                                   xoffset=-320 yoffset=-50@{fg text}

 >would open a shell, offset in x and y (centered) at the current
 >mouse position.

---------------------------------------------------------------

If you use the example above in @{"ToolsDaemon" link "ToolsDaemon.iff/main" 0} to execute a (CLI)command by a
shortcut like <CTRL s> - the @{i}MAGIC@{ui} will be even clearer !
@endnode

