@node "Future" "Future"
@{b}@{fg shadow}T H E   F U T U R E@{ub}@{fg text}



An absolutely wonderful enhancement to make would be to grab the 'lasso'
rectangle coordinates.

How about using a 3 button mouse, with middle button to enable lasso-ing. At
middle-up, a shell could open using the selected rectangle.

I would like to do this lasso-thing, but I don't see no system-friendly manner
of doing it. :(

I know that Snap 2.00 © 1991,  Mikael Karlsson, Absolut Software & Sylvain
ROUGIER is using it's own lasso when grabbing gfx and txt but the source-code
got quite big and complex for that job.

I guess I'll hope for the good guys at AT to implement some support for this.

COME ON Amiga Technologies !!
@endnode

